name: Exeggcute
flavorText: Six of them together form a full-fledged Pokemon. It's often hunted by Crabrawler, but uses psychokinesis to drive it off.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for Exeggcute and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Alolan Exeggutor
flavorText: As it grew taller and taller, it outgrew its reliance on psychic powers, while within it awakened the power of the sleeping dragon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each type of basic Energy card in your discard pile. You can't add more than 100 damage in this way.

name: Alolan Exeggutor
flavorText: As it grew taller and taller, it outgrew its reliance on psychic powers, while within it awakened the power of the sleeping dragon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each type of basic Energy card in your discard pile. You can't add more than 100 damage in this way.

name: Snover
flavorText: In the spring, it grows berries with the texture of frozen treats around its belly.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Fighting Pokemon, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Abomasnow
flavorText: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may attach a Grass Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Scatterbug
flavorText: The powder that covers its body regulates its temperature, so it can live in any region or climate.
Ability1Text: You can use this Ability only if you go second. Once during your first turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for a Spewpa and a Vivillon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Scatterbug
flavorText: The powder that covers its body regulates its temperature, so it can live in any region or climate.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for Vivillon and put it onto this Scatterbug to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Spewpa
flavorText: The beaks of birds can't begin to scratch its stalwart body. To defend itself, it spews powder.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Vivillon
flavorText: The patterns on this Pokemon's wings depend on the climate and topography of its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep and Poisoned.

name: Skiddo
flavorText: If it has sunshine and water, it doesn't need to eat, because it can generate energy from the leaves on its back.
Attack1Text: Attach a Grass Energy card from your hand to this Pokemon.

name: Gogoat
flavorText: They inhabit mountainous regions. The leader of the herd is decided by a battle of clashing horns.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, heal 40 damage from this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon does 30 damage to itself.

name: Pheromosa
flavorText: One of the Ultra Beasts. It refuses to touch anything, perhaps because it senses some uncleanness in this world.
Attack2Text: If you have only 1 Prize card remaining, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Alolan Marowak
flavorText: Its custom is to mourn its lost companions. Mounds of dirt by the side of the road mark the graves of the Marowak.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 basic Energy cards and attach them to your Pokemon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage for each of your Pokemon in play that has Alolan in its name.

name: Heatran
flavorText: Boiling blood, like magma, circulates through its body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Fennekin
flavorText: As it walks, it munches on a twig in place of a snack. It intimidates opponents by puffing hot air out of its ears.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Fennekin
flavorText: As it walks, it munches on a twig in place of a snack. It intimidates opponents by puffing hot air out of its ears.

name: Braixen
flavorText: When the twig is plucked from its tail, friction sets the twig alight. The flame is used to send signals to its allies.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Delphox
flavorText: Using psychic power, it generates a fiery vortex of 5,400 degree Fahrenheit, incinerating foes swept into this whirl of flame.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may leave your opponent's Active Pokemon Burned.
Attack1Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Litleo
flavorText: They set off on their own from their pride and live by themselves to become stronger. These hot-blooded Pokemon are quick to fight.

name: Pyroar
flavorText: With fiery breath of more than 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, they viciously threaten any challenger. The females protect the pride's cubs.
Ability1Text: Whenever your opponent plays an Item or Supporter card from their hand, prevent all effects of that card done to this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: If Lysandre Labs is in play, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Palkia-GX
Attack1Text: Move any number of Energy from your Benched Pokemon to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 more damage times the amount of Water Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Froakie
flavorText: It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon has any Water Energy attached to it, it has no Retreat Cost.

name: Froakie
flavorText: It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.

name: Frogadier
flavorText: Its swiftness is unparalleled. It can scale a tower of more than 2,000 feet in a minute's time.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may put 2 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokemon.

name: Greninja-GX
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may put 3 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokemon.
Attack1Text: You may shuffle this Pokemon and all cards attached to it into your deck.
Attack2Text: This attack does 130 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.) (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Clauncher
flavorText: Through controlled expulsions of internal gas, it can expel water like a pistol shot. At close distances, it can shatter rock.

name: Clawitzer
flavorText: By expelling water from the nozzle in the back of its claw, it can move at a speed of 60 knots.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's Sharpshooting attack does 120 damage instead of 40.
Attack2Text: This attack does 40 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Amaura
flavorText: This calm Pokemon lived in a cold land where there were no violent predators like Tyrantrum.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Aurorus
flavorText: Using its diamond-shaped crystals, it can instantly create a wall of ice to block an opponent's attack.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from Evolution Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon can't attack during your next turn.

name: Bergmite
flavorText: Using air of -150 degrees Fahrenheit, they freeze opponents solid. They live in herds above the snow line on mountains.
Attack1Text: If your opponent has a Stadium card in play, discard it. If you do, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Avalugg
flavorText: The way several Bergmite huddle on its back makes it look like an aircraft carrier made of ice.
Attack1Text: Your opponent can't play any Stadium cards from their hand during their next turn.

name: Volcanion ◇
flavorText: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard a Water Energy card from your hand. If you do, your opponent switches their Active Pokemon with 1 of their Benched Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Dewpider
flavorText: When it comes across enemies or potential prey, this Pokemon smashes its water-bubble-covered head into them.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Araquanid
flavorText: Despite what its appearance suggests, it cares for others. If it finds vulnerable, weak Pokemon, it protectively brings them into its water bubble.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: If 1 of your Pokemon used Bubble during your last turn, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Magnemite
flavorText: It sends out electromagnetic waves, which let it float through the air. Touching it while it's eating electricity will give you a full-body shock.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 Lightning Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Magneton
flavorText: It has about three times the electrical power of Magnemite. For some reason, outbreaks of this Pokemon happen when lots of sunspots appear.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon can't use Zap Cannon during your next turn.

name: Magnezone
flavorText: As it zooms through the sky, this Pokemon seems to be receiving signals of unknown origin, while transmitting signals of unknown purpose.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may attach a Lightning Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon can't use Zap Cannon during your next turn.

name: Helioptile
flavorText: The frills on either side of its head have cells that generate electricity when exposed to sunlight.

name: Heliolisk
flavorText: It stimulates its muscles with electricity, boosting the strength in its legs and enabling it to run 100 yards in five seconds.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Xurkitree
flavorText: It appeared from the Ultra Wormhole. It raided a power plant, so people think it energizes itself with electricity.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: If you have exactly 3 Prize cards remaining, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Rotom
flavorText: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.
Ability1Text: If you have 9 or more Pokemon Tool cards in your discard pile, ignore all Energy in the attack cost of each of this Pokemon's attacks.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon can't attack during your next turn.

name: Uxie
flavorText: It is said that its emergence gave humans the intelligence to improve their quality of life.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokemon's attacks. That Pokemon can't use that attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Mesprit
flavorText: It sleeps at the bottom of a lake. Its spirit is said to leave its body to fly on the lake's surface.
Ability1Text: If you have Azelf in play, your opponent's Pokemon in play have no Resistance.
Attack1Text: If Uxie is on your Bench, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Azelf
flavorText: It is thought that Uxie, Mesprit and Azelf all came from the same egg.
Attack1Text: You can use this attack only if you go second, and only on your first turn. Shuffle 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon and all cards attached to it into their deck.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Espurr
flavorText: It has enough psychic energy to blast everything within 300 feet of itself, but it has no control over its power.
Attack1Text: Move an Energy from 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon to another of their Pokemon.

name: Meowstic
flavorText: The eyeball patterns on the interior of its ears emit psychic energy. It keeps the patterns tightly covered because that power is too immense.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 more damage times the amount of Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Honedge
flavorText: If anyone dares to grab its hilt, it wraps a blue cloth around that person's arm and drains that person's life energy completely.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is your Active Pokemon and is Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack, put 3 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokemon.

name: Honedge
flavorText: If anyone dares to grab its hilt, it wraps a blue cloth around that person's arm and drains that person's life energy completely.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Doublade
flavorText: The complex attack patterns of its two swords are unstoppable, even for an opponent greatly accomplished at swordplay.
Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on each of your opponent's Pokemon that has a Pokemon Tool card attached to it.

name: Aegislash
flavorText: Apparently, it can detect the innate qualities of leadership. According to legend, whoever it recognizes is destined to become king.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, if the Defending Pokemon is damaged by an attack, it will be Knocked Out.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Inkay
flavorText: It flashes the light-emitting spots on its body, which drains its opponent's will to fight. It takes the opportunity to scuttle away and hide.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Malamar
flavorText: It lures prey close with hypnotic motions, then wraps its tentacles around it before finishing it off with digestive fluids.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may attach a Psychic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Skrelp
flavorText: It looks just like rotten kelp. It hides from foes while storing up power for its evolution.

name: Dragalge
flavorText: Tales are told of ships that wander into seas where Dragalge live, never to return.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is your Active Pokemon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if this Pokemon is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokemon is now Poisoned.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon. If both of them are tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Hoopa
flavorText: It gathers things it likes and passes them through its loop to teleport them to a secret place.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Item cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Poipole
flavorText: This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to be chosen as a first partner in its own world.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokemon is Knocked Out, your opponent can't take any Prize cards for it.

name: Naganadel-GX
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each of your Ultra Beasts in play.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Cubone
flavorText: The skull it wears on its head is that of its dead mother. According to some, it will evolve when it comes to terms with the pain of her death.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon can't attack during your next turn.

name: Torterra
flavorText: Small Pokemon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.
Attack1Text: Heal from this Pokemon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage to each of your Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Infernape
flavorText: It tosses its enemies around with agility. It uses all its limbs to fight in its own unique style.
Ability1Text: Put 6 damage counters instead of 2 on your opponent's Burned Pokemon between turns.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Gible
flavorText: It skulks in caves, and when prey or an enemy passes by, it leaps out and chomps them. The force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokemon and put it onto this Pokemon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Gabite
flavorText: Shiny objects are its passion. It can be found in its cave, scarcely moving, its gaze fixed on the jewels it's amassed or Carbink it has caught.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokemon and put it onto this Pokemon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Garchomp
flavorText: The protuberances on its head serve as sensors. It can even detect distant prey.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: If you played Cynthia from your hand during this turn, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Croagunk
flavorText: Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Toxicroak
flavorText: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.
Attack2Text: If any of your Psychic Pokemon were Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack during their last turn, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: Pancham
flavorText: There's no point to the leaf in its mouth, aside from an effort to look cool. It's mischievous, so it's not well suited to inexperienced Trainers.
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon has any Darkness Energy attached to it, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Binacle
flavorText: They stretch and then contract, yanking their rocks along with them in bold hops. They eat seaweed that washes up on the shoreline.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Barbaracle
flavorText: Barbaracle's legs and hands have minds of their own, and they will move independently. But they usually follow the head's orders.
Attack1Text: If you have exactly 7 cards in your hand, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Tyrunt
flavorText: Its immense jaws have enough destructive force that it can chew up an automobile. It lived 100 million years ago.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Tyrantrum
flavorText: Nothing could stop this Pokemon 100 million years ago, so it behaved like a king.
Ability1Text: As long as you don't have more Pokemon in play than your opponent, this Pokemon's attacks do 60 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance), and it takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Hawlucha
flavorText: With its wings, it controls its position in the air. It likes to attack from above, a maneuver that is difficult to defend against.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 less damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokemon's Retreat Cost.

name: Zygarde
flavorText: This is Zygarde's form when about 10% of its cells have been gathered. It runs across the land at speeds greater than 60 mph.
Ability1Text: Damage from this Pokemon's attacks isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.
Attack1Text: If your opponent has an Ultra Beast in play, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Zygarde
flavorText: It's thought to be monitoring the ecosystem. There are rumors that even greater power lies hidden within it.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: If you have used your GX attack, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Zygarde-GX
Attack1Text: Attach 2 Fighting Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokemon.

name: Diancie ◇
flavorText: It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is on your Bench, your Fighting Pokemon's attacks do 20 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from each of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Rockruff
flavorText: This Pokemon has lived with people since times long ago. It can sense when its Trainer is in the dumps and will stick close by its Trainer's side.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Lycanroc
flavorText: Bathed in the setting sun of evening, Lycanroc has undergone a special kind of evolution. An intense fighting spirit underlies its calmness.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.

name: Buzzwole
flavorText: A mysterious life-form called an Ultra Beast. Witnesses saw it pulverize a dump truck with a single punch.
Attack1Text: If your opponent has exactly 4 Prize cards remaining, this attack does 90 more damage.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.

name: Pangoro
flavorText: From the slight twitches of its bamboo leaf, it deduces its opponent's movements. It's eager to tussle but kindhearted toward its companions.
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon has any damage counters on it, this attack does 50 more damage, and both Active Pokemon are now Confused.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 more damage for each heads.

name: Yveltal-GX
Attack1Text: Heal from this Pokemon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Guzzlord
flavorText: A dangerous Ultra Beast, it appears to be eating constantly, but for some reason its droppings have never been found.
Attack1Text: If you have exactly 2, 4, or 6 Prize cards remaining, discard the top 10 cards of your deck.

name: Empoleon
flavorText: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each Benched Pokemon (both yours and your opponent's).
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Dialga-GX
Attack1Text: Draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Flabebe
flavorText: When it finds a flower it likes, it dwells on that flower its whole life long. It floats in the wind's embrace with an untroubled heart.
Ability1Text: If you go second, this Pokemon can evolve during your first turn.

name: Flabebe
flavorText: When it finds a flower it likes, it dwells on that flower its whole life long. It floats in the wind's embrace with an untroubled heart.
Attack1Text: Shuffle 3 in any combination of Pokemon and basic Energy cards from your discard pile into your deck.

name: Floette
flavorText: When the flowers of a well-tended flower bed bloom, it appears and celebrates with an elegant dance.
Attack1Text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon with their Active Pokemon. If you do, switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Florges
flavorText: In times long past, governors of castles would invite Florges to create flower gardens to embellish the castle domains.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, put an Item card from your discard pile on top of your deck.
Attack1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from Dragon Pokemon during your opponent's next turn.

name: Sylveon
flavorText: When this Pokemon sights its prey, it swirls its ribbonlike feelers as a distraction. A moment later, it pounces.
Attack1Text: Your opponent reveals their hand. You may discard a Supporter card you find there and use the effect of that card as the effect of this attack.

name: Dedenne
flavorText: It uses its tail to absorb electricity from power plants or from outlets in houses, and then it fires the electricity from its whiskers.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Pokemon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: If you have any Lightning Pokemon on your Bench, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Klefki
flavorText: It inserts its horn into chinks in metal, absorbing metal ions. For some reason, it collects keys.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Xerneas-GX
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Goomy
flavorText: Its source of protection is its slimy, germ-laden mucous membrane. Anyone who touches it needs some thorough hand-washing.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is your Active Pokemon, your opponent's Pokemon's attacks cost Colorless more.

name: Goomy
flavorText: Its source of protection is its slimy, germ-laden mucous membrane. Anyone who touches it needs some thorough hand-washing.
Attack2Text: This attack does 10 damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon.

name: Sliggoo
flavorText: This Pokemon's mucous can dissolve anything. Toothless, it sprays mucous on its prey. Once they're nicely dissolved, it slurps them up.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Goodra
flavorText: It gets picked on because it's meek. But then, whoever teased it gets to feel the full force of its horns and a good swatting from its thick tail.
Ability1Text: Whenever you attach a Water Energy card from your hand to this Pokemon, heal 20 damage from it.
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon was healed during this turn, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Ultra Necrozma-GX
Attack1Text: Discard all basic Psychic Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 80 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.
Attack2Text: You can use this attack only if the total of both players' remaining Prize cards is 6 or less. Put 6 damage counters on each of your opponent's Pokemon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Arceus ◇
flavorText: It is told in mythology that this Pokemon was born before the universe even existed.
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of your opponent's attacks, except damage, done to this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: You can use this attack only if you have Grass, Water, and Lightning Pokemon on your Bench. Search your deck for up to 3 basic Energy cards and attach them to your Pokemon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Bunnelby
flavorText: It has ears like shovels. Digging holes strengthens its ears so much that they can sever thick roots effortlessly.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Diggersby
flavorText: As powerful as an excavator, its ears can reduce dense bedrock to rubble. When it's finished digging, it lounges lazily.
Attack1Text: You may do 40 more damage. If you do, discard the top 2 cards of your deck.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 80 damage for each heads.

name: Furfrou
flavorText: Historically, in the Kalos region, these Pokemon were the designated guardians of the king.
Attack1Text: You may draw cards until you have 5 cards in your hand.

name: Noibat
flavorText: Even a robust wrestler will become dizzy and unable to stand when exposed to its 200,000-hertz ultrasonic waves.
Attack2Text: Your opponent reveals their hand. Discard all Item cards you find there.

name: Noivern
flavorText: The ultrasonic waves it emits from its ears can reduce a large boulder to pebbles. It swoops out of the dark to attack.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is Confused, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: Palkia-GX
Attack1Text: Move any number of Energy from your Benched Pokemon to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 more damage times the amount of Water Energy attached to this Pokemon.

Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may put 3 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokemon.

Attack2Text: This attack does 130 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.) (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Naganadel-GX
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each of your Ultra Beasts in play.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Lucario-GX
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon evolved from Riolu during this turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Zygarde-GX
Attack1Text: Attach 2 Fighting Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokemon.

name: Yveltal-GX
Attack1Text: Heal from this Pokemon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Dialga-GX
Attack1Text: Draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Xerneas-GX
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Ultra Necrozma-GX
Attack1Text: Discard all basic Psychic Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 80 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.
Attack2Text: You can use this attack only if the total of both players' remaining Prize cards is 6 or less. Put 6 damage counters on each of your opponent's Pokemon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

Attack1Text: Move any number of Energy from your Benched Pokemon to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 more damage times the amount of Water Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Greninja-GX
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may put 3 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokemon.
Attack1Text: You may shuffle this Pokemon and all cards attached to it into your deck.
Attack2Text: This attack does 130 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.) (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Naganadel-GX
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each of your Ultra Beasts in play.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Lucario-GX
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon evolved from Riolu during this turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Zygarde-GX
Attack1Text: Attach 2 Fighting Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokemon.

name: Yveltal-GX
Attack1Text: Heal from this Pokemon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Dialga-GX
Attack1Text: Draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Xerneas-GX
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Ultra Necrozma-GX
Attack1Text: Discard all basic Psychic Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 80 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.
Attack2Text: You can use this attack only if the total of both players' remaining Prize cards is 6 or less. Put 6 damage counters on each of your opponent's Pokemon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)
